 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-rnase","title":"[REVIEW-P2][HIGH] fcp-oauth PKCE gate still accepts static code_verifier from config","description":"crates/fcp-oauth/src/oauth2.rs:501-508 and 529-556 still treat self.config.extra_token_params.contains_key("code_verifier") as sufficient to satisfy use_pkce, even after 4b0dd8b7 reordered the merge so exchange_code_with_pkce() wins on conflict. Bug scenario: a connector can configure a fixed or attacker-influenced code_verifier once via with_token_param("code_verifier", ...), call exchange_code() with use_pkce=true, and the library will send that static verifier on every auth-code exchange without requiring the per-session Pkce generated during authorization_url[_with_pkce](). That defeats RFC 7636 proof-of-possession because the verifier is no longer bound to the specific authorization session. Suggested fix: when use_pkce is true, reject config-supplied code_verifier entirely (or require exchange_code_with_pkce / AuthorizationGrant) and add a regression test that exchange_code() errors even if extra_token_params contains code_verifier.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-23T20:15:27.115077Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-23T20:27:09.710904Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T20:27:09.710127Z","close_reason":"Rejected static code_verifier config and enforced per-flow PKCE","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
